<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[155,794,164,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[177,317,501,520]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[342,493,500,522]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspersum">
<emphasis box="[342,493,500,522]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Solanum aspersum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in widely separated and isolated populations along the Andes from central Ecuador into Colombia in both the Cordillera Occidental and the Cordillera Central, from 
<quantity box="[296,456,584,606]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="m" value="2050.0" valueMax="2500.0" valueMin="1600.0">1600 to 2500 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[155,794,164,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[177,298,614,633]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the few and scattered collections of this species (aspersus = scattered) along the Andes from Ecuador to Colombia that have been subsumed in the more common 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dunal" box="[344,484,696,718]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aureum">
<emphasis box="[344,484,696,718]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Solanum aureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[155,794,164,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[177,542,726,745]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Preliminary conservation status.</emphasis>
Although known from very few herbarium specimens, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[462,560,752,774]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspersum">
<emphasis box="[462,560,752,774]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. aspersum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a wide distribution, and is possibly more common in its total range than currently known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
